<HEADLINE> Mohammed Rashid to Be Released From Greek Prison </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Convicted Palestinian terrorist
Mohammed Rashid is to be released from prison after serving
three-fifths of a 16-year term in Greece for a bomb attack against
an American airliner in August 1982.
</P>
<P>
According to the terms of a local judicial council decision,
Rashid will upon release be immediately expelled from the country
for life.
</P>
<P>
Rashid, 46, was arrested at Athens airport in 1988 following a
tip-off from U.S. authorities.
</P>
<P>
He was convicted of premeditated homicide and planting a bomb
in the Hawaii-bound Pan American airliner. A Japanese teenager was
killed and 15 other passengers were injured as a result of the
explosion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
