<HEADLINE> Malawian Minister on Regional Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The globalisation of the world
economy has demonstrated to the southern African countries the need
to speed up regional integration and survive in a highly competitive
environment, Malawian Minister of Transport Harry Thompson said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing delegates at the Beira Corridor development conference
in Harare, Tompson said it was now evident that no single country
could ''do it alone'' in the globalised world market.
</P>
<P>
He said competition was fierce and to be competitive, countries
had to make timeous delivery of their goods.
</P>
<P>
''The concept of having a development corridor is a welcome move
for us in Malawi. This will spread development in our country and
also increase cross-border trade and investment.''
</P>
<P>
The Beira Corridor is a railway and road network running
between the Zimbabwean eastern border town of Mutare and the
Mozambican port city of Beira.
</P>
<P>
''The Malawian government has supported and will continue to
support Mozambique in rehabilitating the remaining kilometres near
Malawi,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the Malawi government supported the Beira corridor
development conference initiative and believed it would mutually
benefit the peoples of the countries involved and also the entire
region. enditem

