<HEADLINE> World Bank to Release 200 Million Dlrs to Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank is likely to
release an additional tranche of 200 million US dollars to
Pakistan for balance of payment support next month above its
annual lending program.
</P>
<P>
"Its release in a single tranche would be an exception to the
previous practice, when such disbursement was used to be made in
two to three tranches in as many years," sources from Pakistan's
Finance Minister said.
</P>
<P>
The release of fund would be made on the fast disbursement
basis, reflecting confidence of the International donor agencies
over the fiscal and monetary reforms and its implementation in
Pakistan, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank's annual lending program to Pakistan involves
about 650 million dollars and the release of fund amounting to
around 200 million dollars would be in addition to that.
</P>
<P>
Senior Pakistani officials held extensive talks with the
representatives of the World Bank in Islamabad recently on
boosting the country's banking and financial sector.
</P>
<P>
"These would now be finalized in Washington next week," sources
said. "The cabinet has already approved these reform measures to
be discussed with the donor agency."
</P>
<P>
Advisor to the Prime Minister on Finance and Economic Affairs
Shahid Burki is leading a high-level Pakistani delegation for
talks with the International Monetary Fund and the World Bank in
Washington next week.
</P>
<P>
The sources also denied that the reform measures were being
taken under the pressure from the World Bank.  
</P>
</TEXT>
