<HEADLINE> Good Transport System Urged in SADC Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Regional Road Freight
Association (RRFA) today said good transport systems are necessary
for the socio-economic development of the Southern African
Development Community (SADC) region.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the two-day Beira Development Corridor (bdc)
Conference being held in harare, RRFA Chairman Shadreck Matsimbe said
there was need for sound transport infrastructure in the region to
ensurfe the smooth flow of both rail and road traffic.
</P>
<P>
Already, he said, motorised road transport within the region moved
close to 80 percent of people and goods because of its flexibility.
</P>
<P>
He said the Beira Corridor was a convinient route as it was the
shortest route to the sea for most of southern Africa's land-locked
countries.
</P>
<P>
He stressed, certain portions of the region's roads are in
good, some in poor and others in a worse state, and it is important
to address these issues if we are to develop the region.
</P>
<P>
He expressed satisfaction with the improvement of the
security system in Mozambique in the past three years. enditem


