<HEADLINE> Russian Coal Miners Stage Strike, Urge Pay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Russian coal miners downed
tools today in an indefinite strike over demands for months of unpaid
wages, a miners union leader said.
</P>
<P>
Vitaly Budko, chairman of the Russian Coalminers' Union, told
reporters here that about 400,000 miners, from 154 out of
the country's 189 mines, were involved in the strike.
</P>
<P>
In addition to back wages of 1.5 trillion rubles (270 million
U.S. dollars), the strikers are demanding the resignation of the
government, which has failed to "ensure the timely payment of
wages," said Budko.
</P>
<P>
He revealed that he had been invited to attend a Cabinet meeting
scheduled for Thursday, which is to focus on the situation in the
coal industry.
</P>
<P>
Weighed down by debt, the Russian government has failed to pay
state workers for months. Two days earlier, about 20,000 teachers
in the far east stopped work for several hours in protest over
unpaid wages. 
</P>
