<HEADLINE> US Post Office Collects 1.6 Bln Dlr Profit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Post Office today
announced a profit of nearly 1.6 billion U.S. dollars in fiscal
1996, the second successive year the agency won over a billion
dollar profit.
</P>
<P>
The gainings are attributed to the rate increase to 32 cents
for first-class mail that took effect in 1995 and mail volume
growth which also boosted the agency's income.
</P>
<P>
The office's performance was just 200 million dollars less than
1995's record earnings, "the best financial one-two punch in our
history," Postmaster General Marvin Runyon said.
</P>
<P>
The Postal Service posted total income of 56.4 billion dollars
in fiscal 1996, which ended on September 30 and a record volume of
182.7 billion pieces of mail.
</P>
<P>
In the previous fiscal year, the office earned a 1.77 billion
dollar profit, the first year profit since 1989 and also the
highest one recorded in its history. 
</P>
