<HEADLINE> Chirac Vows to Fight Terrorism After Train Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 3 (Xinhua) -- President Jacques Chirac vowed
this evening to fight terrorism after a bomb explosion killed two
people and wounded at least eight gravely on a train in downtown
Paris this evening.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Alain Juppe and Interior Minister Jean-Louis
Debre have confirmed that the explosion was caused by a bomb.
</P>
<P>
"It is soon afterwards established that it was a bomb of very
strong power," Juppe said, adding that he could not provide any
details.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the bomb could be a 13-kilogram heavy gas
demijohn which is usually resorted to by Islamic extremists in
Algeria.
</P>
<P>
However, other extremist groups, such as the FLNC-Canal
Historique of Corsica and the Basque separatist group of ETA, are
also likely to be the terrorist attacker in the explosion, which
greatly shocked the French capital this evening.
</P>
<P>
The station of Port Royal for the express railway network for
Paris and its suburbs, near the famous Luxembourg Park, is now
heavily guarded by paramilitary police and anti-riot police, as
ambulances and fire engines whistled through the streets nearby.
</P>
<P>
Twenty other people were more lightly wounded while hospital
sources described three people as in a desperate situation.
</P>
<P>
Interior Minister Debre said that he would call a meeting of
security forces and he had ordered a strengthening of checking
suspects at the frontiers. 
</P>
