University printing office, Secret Service agents disclosed
Monday.
</P>
<P>
More than 80,000 in 20 U.S. dollar bills have been
counterfeited in the printing office in the basement of journalism
building in Morningside Heights, hundreds of which have been
passed in bars, restaurants and other places of business around
New York City, the agents were quoted today by the New York Times
as saying.
</P>
