computers and copiers have been used to embezzle funds, forge
identity cards, create bogus tickets and plagiarize the classics,
the newspaper commented.
</P>
<P>
Further arrests might be expected in an inquiry that began last
May, when the first of the bogus 20 u.s. dollar bills began
showing up around the city, said Brian F. Gimlettt, the special
agent in charge of the Secret Service New York field office.
</P>
<P>
The penalties range up to 15 years in prison upon conviction.
