<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Nigeria Step up Ties in Higher Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 3 (Xinhua) -- China and Nigeria today signed
an agreement to strengthen cooperation in the field of higher
education.
</P>
<P>
Under the accord, which was inked in Nigeria's capital of
Abuja, the Chinese government will provide a number of computers
and related equipment to the Yaba College of Technology and the
Edo State University in the 1996-1997 academic year.
</P>
<P>
The two Nigerian universities will establish a computer
laboratory and improve teaching conditions, Dai Xingyuan,
cultural councillor of the Chinese embassy in Nigeria told Xinhua
today.
</P>
<P>
China will also send three teachers of computer science to
Nigeria to help install and commission the equipment, and help
train Nigerian teachers and technicians, according to the pact
signed by Chinese ambassador to Nigeria Lu Fengding and Nigerian
Minister of Education M. T. Liman.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also agreed to further cooperation in higher
education and other fields in the future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
