<HEADLINE> Formation of New Energy Ministry Pushed In Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Newly-appointed Thai Industry
Minister Korn Dabbaransi said he would push for the establishment
of a new energy ministry to consolidate all government units
responsible for the sector.
</P>
<P>
The formation of a new energy ministry is part of the new Thai
government's policy to be delivered in Parliament from December 11
to 13. Currently, there are nine departments involved in energy
affairs at seven ministries.
</P>
<P>
Korn was quoted by local daily The Nation as saying that a
separate ministry will increase energy management efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Korn also supported further expansion of the oil-refining
sector and suggested the Petroleum Authority of Thailand have its
own refinery. The authority currently owns a major interest in
four of the six refineries in the country.  
</P>
