<HEADLINE> Thai Baht Drops to Four-Year Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Thai baht declined to a
nearly four-year low Tuesday upon the poor economic data released
by the Bank of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The US dollar was traded with the baht at the midrate of 25.56,
the highest level since January 1993, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The drop came after data from the Thai central bank last week
showed a 9.3 percent decline in exports in September and a mere
0.9 percent rise in export growth year-on-year for the first nine
months of this year. 
</P>
