<HEADLINE> U.S. Serviceman Sentenced to 13 Years for Attempted Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Nagasaki District Court
Wednesday meted out a 13-year jail sentence to a U.S. serviceman
for attempted murder and robbery last July 16 of a Japanese woman
in the city of Sasebo, Nagasaki Prefecture in the country, Kyodo
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Under to the ruling, Terrence Swanson, 20, a crew member of the
3,638-ton U.S. guided-missile frigate McClusky, attacked the woman
from behind in a parking lot in the port city, slashed her throat
and stole 13,000 yen from her handbag. The woman was seriously
injured.
</P>
<P>
Swanson was handed over to Japanese police in line with a
Japan-U.S. agreement reached in October last year to turn over
U.S. soldiers, suspected in serious criminal cases, even before
they are indicted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
