<HEADLINE> Akayev Orders Government Reshuffle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Kyrgyz President Askar Akayev
ordered a cabinet reshuffle Tuesday, axing its 22 ministries to 16
to cut down government expenses and improve management, said
reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Former Minister of Finance Kemelbek Nanayev was appointed as
first Deputy Prime Minister to replace Addyzhapar Tagayev, who
became President of the National Market of Negotiable Securities.
</P>
<P>
Former ministries of geology, and tourism and sports will be
changed into self-supporting departments.
</P>
<P>
The ministries of economy, communications and water conservancy
are respectively incorporated into those of finance, post and
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Education is now merged into the Ministry of
Science and Culture.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet keeps the posts of the First Deputy Prime Minister
and two Deputy Prime Ministers.
</P>
<P>
A total of 3,040 officials will be reduced from the present
staff of 17,894 working at all levels of the administration.
</P>
</TEXT>
