<HEADLINE> Thai Deputy PM Assures More Freedom for Capital Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Thai Deputy Prime Minister
Amnuay Virawan Tuesday assured that the local capital market would
be free from political interference.
</P>
<P>
The position would be part of the government's economic policy,
said the deputy prime minister whom Prime Minister Chavalit
Yongchaiyudh has given more free hand in handling the country's
economic affairs.
</P>
<P>
Amnuay made these remarks when he and his economic team
accompanied Chavalit on a visit to the Stock Exchange of Thailand
on the day in a bid to boost the confidence of the investors.
</P>
<P>
Promising to work on improving trading liquidity and reducing
the prevailing bearishness on the stock market over the next six
months, Amnuay said that he would aim to solve liquidity problems
in the property and financial businesses.
</P>
<P>
The deputy prime minister also wanted to make local mechanism
effective enough to stabilize the baht, local newspapers said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors in July speculated that the baht would be
devalued on the belief that the Thai government wanted to help its
ailing export business, which caused heavy selling of the baht and
massive outflow of foreign capital.
</P>
<P>
The Thai central bank had to step in to ease the situation by
selling dollar-baht swap options.  
</P>
</TEXT>
