<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka To Launch Food Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 4 (Xinhua)-- Sri Lanka will launch a
countrywide food drive this month, aiming to come to terms with
the world food shortage in year 2005 predicted by the Food and
Agricultural Organization.
</P>
<P>
Officials have been directed to give the highest priority to
this drive and have been briefed on the type of food crops that
should be cultivated and the follow up action to be taken,
Agrarian Services Commission sources said today.
</P>
<P>
Uncultivated bare lands will be acquired and used for the
drive. Notices have been issued in respect of 30,000 uncultivated
plots of land giving time for their owners to show why they have
failed to cultivate them, and 5,000 persons have been instructed
to immediately cultivate their lands or lose possession, the
sources stated.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's rice production is over 2.6 million metric tons.
The country has to import food annually to meet the shortage. Sri
Lanka has imported 500,000 metric tons of rice this year due to
drought.  
</P>
</TEXT>
