<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines' Exports Up 17.5 Percent in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' exports in
October grew 17.5 percent to 1.88 billion U.S. dollars from last
year's 1.6 billion dollars, the National Statistics Office said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The office said that electronics and components continued to be
the country's top earner, accounting for 41 percent of the month's
total exports revenue and registering a 31 percent increase over
the same month of last year.
</P>
<P>
The second biggest earner for the month was articles of apparel
and clothing accessories which recorded an aggregate income of 188
million U.S. dollars, said the office.
</P>
<P>
The United States was still the number one export market of the
Philippines, the office said. It was followed by Japan, the
Netherlands, Singapore and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
For the whole period from January to October, the value of
exports grew 16.7 percent to 16.8 billion U.S. dollars from 14.4
billion in the same period last year, the office said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
