<HEADLINE> Chinese President Leaves Pakistan for Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAHORE, Pakistan, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President
Jiang Zemin left here this morning for Nepal after winding up his
four-day state visit to Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani President Farooq Leghari, Punjab Provincial Governor
Khawja Ahmed Tariq Rahim, Punjab Chief Minister Mohammad Afzal
Hayat and Chinese Ambassador Zhang Chengli saw the Chinese
president and his entourage off at the airport.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Pakistan, Jiang held wide-ranging talks with
Leghari and met with caretaker Prime Minister Malik Miraj Khalid
and other high government officials.
</P>
<P>
The two countries signed seven agreements for closer
cooperation in various fields. Jiang and his Pakistani counterpart
Leghari were present at the signing ceremony. Both sides
emphasized the need to further develop the existing friendly
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president also addressed Pakistan's Senate on
China's policy towards South Asia. Jiang also visited Lahore, the
cultural center of Pakistan, where he was again accorded a warm
welcome and a grand reception.
</P>
<P>
Nepal is the last leg of Jiang's four-nation tour which also
took him to the Philippines and India. 
</P>
</TEXT>
