<HEADLINE> Sino-US Business School Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Municipal Education
Committee has approved the establishment of the city's first
joint-venture independent business school, today's "China Daily"
reported.
</P>
<P>
Beijing China-USA Business University will be set up by JP
International Inc, a US-based consulting service and trade
company, and Beijing Jianshe University, with the US side
controlling 95 percent of the school's equity.
</P>
<P>
As a non-governmental school, Beijing Jianshe University was
founded eight years ago by the Jiusan Society, one of China's
eight non-communist democratic parties.
</P>
<P>
Management plans to invest four million US dollars in the
school in its first development stage, buying computers and other
educational facilities, the report quoted a source from JP
International Inc. as saying.
</P>
<P>
The school is expected to start its courses in March
1997. Courses will cover international trade and business,
international finance and management, and quality control.
</P>
<P>
The school would mainly offer classroom teaching as well as
long-distance courses in Western standard business education to
existing staff in foreign representative offices or joint
ventures, the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
