<HEADLINE> Indonesia Predicted to Win Three Titles in Badminton GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia is predicted to win
three titles at least from the world badminton Grand Prix final to
be open Wednesday in Denpasar, Bali of Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Soerjadi, chairman of the Indonesian Badminton Federation
(PBSI), said here Tuesday that the host country aimed at three
titles at the men's singles and doubles, and mixed doubles.
</P>
<P>
He did not speculate on the winner of the women's singles
although the host country will field top women players Susi
Susanti and Mia Audina.
</P>
<P>
The 350,000 U.S. dollars Grand Prix final features 16 men's and
12 women's singles players and eight doubles pairs.
</P>
<P>
Soejadi said that the federation did not give a special target
for players, but hopefully they would play as best as possible.
</P>
<P>
He also said Chinese Dong Jiong and Ye Zhaoying are their
strongest rivals in the men's and women's singles competitions and
Malaysia's Cheah Soon Kit and Yap Kim Hock and China's Ge Fei and
Gu Jun are serious contenders for the doubles titles. 
</P>
