<HEADLINE> Russia, Iran to Enhance Cooperation in Energy Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials of Russia and
Iran vowed here today to strengthen cooperation in the field of
energy resources between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Russian experts are now readying an atomic power plant at
Bushehr on Iran's Gulf coast for operation, said Russian Foreign
Trade Minister Oleg Davydov, who is also Chairman of an economic
cooperation commission between Russia and Iran, Itar-Tass news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Davydov said that Russia will provide Iran with nuclear
reactors, under the supervision of the International Atomic Energy
Agency, that will not be used for military purpose.
</P>
<P>
Russia and Iran have bright prospect in the cooperation of
construction of power stations, petrochemical installations and a
canal linking the Caspian Sea and the Gulf, he added.
</P>
<P>
The implementation of these projects will raise the
Russian-Iranian bilateral trade volume to the level of billions of
U.S. dollars, Davydov said.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Finance Minister Morteza Mohammad-Khan, who is also the
chairman of the commission on the Iranian side, said Iran will
coordinate strategy with Russia to open up its gas resources and
place them in the world markets. The two countries will form an
alliance in occupying major world markets of fuels in the next
century, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
