<HEADLINE> Insurer Grabs Power Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- A leading Chinese property
insurer has announced that it has underwritten an insurance policy
for 500 million US dollars to transport freight for Huaneng
international Power Development Corp (HIPDC).
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement signed last Friday, People's
Insurance (Property) Co (PICC Property) would provide insurance
for HIPDC to transport imported equipment to be used on power
projects in Nantong, Jiangsu Province and Fuzhou, Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
HIPDC, which was set up in 1985, is a major investor in China's
power industry. It has launched thermal power plants and
hydroelectric stations across the country.
</P>
<P>
To date, PICC Property, as the largest property insurer in
China, has offered insurance coverage for HIPDC's overseas freight
transportation and machine damage, all risk for project
installation and property insurance.
</P>
<P>
The accumulated amount of insurance has topped ten billion US
dollars, 4.26 billion of which was for the transportation of
freight. 
</P>
