<HEADLINE> Japan Gives Soft Loans to Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia and Japan exchanged
diplomatic notes Tuesday on Japan's overseas developmental
assistance (ODA) loans worth 190.1 billion yen (1.96 billion US
dollars) to fund Indonesia's development projects.
</P>
<P>
The loans constitute the main portion of the total ODA amount
of 206.6 billion yen (2.13 billion US dollars) to Indonesia for
the 1996/1997 fiscal year, an official of the Indonesian Foreign
Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the loans mature in 30 years, including a
10-year grace period.
</P>
<P>
There will be a 2.3 to 2.7 percent annual interest rate on the
loans to fund 23 projects on energy, education, infrastructure,
agriculture, transportation and irrigation, said the official.
