<HEADLINE> Bulgaria to Provide Loan to Vitalize Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Bulgarian National Foundation
for Agriculture Tuesday announced that it will give out a loan of
4 billion lev (some 16 million U.S. dollars) to promote
agricultural production in the coming winter and next spring.
</P>
<P>
Half of the loan will be used to transform and develop the
agricultural structure while the other half will go to purchase of
farming machines and tools to develop animal husbandry and crops
planting, said the foundation.
</P>
<P>
In order to encourage farming communes and individual farmers
to draw the loan, two commercial banks in charge of the loan have
decided to lower interest rate to 36 percent by cutting more than
20 percent.
</P>
<P>
Local media attributed the loan to a shortfall in agricultural
output this year.
</P>
<P>
The wheat-growing area has decreased with wheat output hitting
the lowerest point last summer in the past 10 years, leading to a
food crisis, short supply of forage crops and serious recession in
animal husbandry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
