<HEADLINE> Ukraine to Support Disabled People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine will provide disabled
people with enough tools such as orthopedic limbs and wheelchairs,
Ukrainian Prime Minister Pavel Lazarenko said on the International
Invalids' Day which falls today.
</P>
<P>
Lazarenko said when visiting the National Experimental Factory
of Orthopedic Limbs that factories serving invalids would not only
enjoy favorable treatment but also more funds from the government.
</P>
<P>
The government will discuss how to improve the quality of
orthopedic tools in February next year and will give extra funds
to produce motorized wheelchairs for the disabled, he said.
</P>
<P>
Among the 2.2 million invalids in Ukraine, 254,000 were
disabled in World War II, 6,800 hurt by the Chernobyl disaster and
1.5 million injured at work. 
</P>
