<HEADLINE> 3 Killed in Rebels' Attack on Philippine Troops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- A soldier and two civilians were
killed Tuesday morning in a heavy fighting between government
troops and Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) guerrillas in the
southern Philippines, according to the military.
</P>
<P>
The military said the Moro rebels attacked the Army's 32nd
Infantry Brigade in Sirawai town in Zamboanga del Norte province
when it was conducting an operation. The two civilians were the
brigade's guides in the operation.
</P>
<P>
The attack Tuesday was the third in six days staged by MILF
fighters on the government troops in the province.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, MILF rebels killed a security officer in a second
attack at a logging camp in Sirawai town and then shot dead four
soldiers of the 32nd Infantry Battalion sent to the camp in an
ambush.
</P>
<P>
On November 28, rebels killed two camp guards and wounded five
others. Another guard was taken hostage to prevent soldiers from
capturing the retreating rebels.
</P>
<P>
Police say the rebels are demanding money from the logging
company in exchange for continued peaceful operations.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here said the renewed fighting will further postpone
the exploratory peace talks between the government and the MILF.
The planned peace talks have been delayed by the MILF for several
times after the government refused to stop offensive against its
bases on Basilan Island and withdraw troops from the MILF-claimed
areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
