<HEADLINE> Guangdong Vows to Help Guangxi Shake Off Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province, one of the
most developed areas in Chinna, has pledged to help free
neighboring Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region from poverty.
</P>
<P>
Xie Fei, secretary of the Guangdong Provincial Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), made the pledge during his visit
to Guangxi November 26-29.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong and Guangxi have been paired by the central
government to carry out the primary stage of the country's
poverty-eradication campaign.
</P>
<P>
Xie, who is also a member of the Political Bureau of the CPC
Central Committee, led a Guangdong delegation to Guangxi, and a
series of talks was held between local leaders from the two
coastal provinces.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong, which also has underdeveloped areas of its own, is
experienced in dealing with poverty eradication, and the two
provinces can learn from each other in this respect, according to
Xie.
</P>
<P>
In 1997 provincial and local governments in Guangdong will
provide 60 million yuan gratis to Baise and Hechi prefectures in
Guangxi for the resettlement of poor people.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong will also employ more laborers from Guangxi and help
its neighbor train local cadres.
</P>
<P>
The two provinces will encourage local enterprises to conduct
more economic exchanges and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Guangdong side said that it favors the idea of
holding a Guangxi investment invitation fair in Guangzhou,
Guangdong's provincial capital.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
