<HEADLINE> Trial Digital Microwave Network In East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- China will set up a pilot
digital microwave network in Shandong Province to speed up
digitalization of its long-distance telecoms.
</P>
<P>
According to "People's Posts and Telecommunications News", a
high-capacity SDH (synchronous digital hierarchy) microwave
network will connect Yutai and Sishui, via Jining City.
</P>
<P>
The network is being developed by the No. 4 Research Institute
of the Ministry of Post and Telecommunications. It is 150 km long
and can provide a transmission speed of 155 Mb/s, the highest for
its kind in the world.
</P>
<P>
In addition to testing the feasibility of domestic
SDH microwave equipment, the network will accelerate the
commercialization of microwave transmission technology in
China, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The Shandong Provincial Post and Telecommunications
Administration has signed a cooperation agreement with the
institute, and will offer capital and labor support for the
project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
