<HEADLINE> UN: 133 Million Dollars Needed for Humanitarian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations said here
today that 133 million US dollars are needed for humanitarian aid
to war-torn Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The UN appeal, which has been prepared in consultation with UN
agencies, non-governmental organizations and the donor community,
will provide urgent humanitarian assistance and address the needs
for rehabilitation and reconstruction throughout Afghanistan,
according to the UN Department of Humanitarian Affairs (DHA).
</P>
<P>
The DHA said that some 500,000 people in the Afghan capital of
Kabul alone will depend on food relief to survive this winter
while the eighteenth winter at war comes to Afghanistan.
Furthermore, the recent civil conflict has worsened the already
difficult living conditions in the country that has the highest
rates of infant, childhood and maternal mortality in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The DHA called on the international community to respond
generously to the appeal to relieve the suffering of the Afghan
people and to provide a basis for longer-term rehabilitation and
reconstruction of the country with nearly 10 million landmines
constantly causing death and disability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
