<HEADLINE> French Army Put on Alert after Terrorist Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The French Army in the Paris
region has been put on alert to help police and paramilitary
police carry out the "Vigipirate Operation" in hunting down the
terrorists who blew up a Paris train this evening.
</P>
<P>
The chief of staff of the Paris Military Region have been
ordered by the army headquarters to respond to all requests any
time to participate in the anti-terrorist operation, the Agence
France Presse (AFP) quoted military sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
General Michel Billot, Military Commander of the Paris Region,
or l'Ile-de-France, is reportedly following the situation very
closely.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 1,000 elite mobile paramilitary police, the CRS, are
being dispatched to Paris to guard all strategic positions and all
railway stations, in a reinforcement of the Paris police force.
</P>
<P>
Police will intensify patrol in the streets of the capital, and
will interview anyone they think can help them find the attacker.
</P>
<P>
Interior Minister Jean-Louis Debre was chairing an emergency
session of security officers tonight, which was joined by General
Yves Capdepont, number two of the national paramilitary police,
the Gendarmerie.
</P>
<P>
AFP quoted police as saying that the gas demijohn bomb, the
type frequently used by Algerian Islamic extremists, was placed on
the fourth car of the eight-car RER train, which served Paris and
its suburbs.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-eight people were hospitalized after being wounded by
the explosion, among whom several were in a desperate situation,
according to hospital sources.
</P>
<P>
Two people were killed instantly by the powerful bomb
explosion, which took place at 1803 (1603GMT) when the train was
entering the platform of a RER station near Luxembourg Park in
downtown Paris. 
</P>
</TEXT>
